author: David McCollum
title: CHS boys finish 3rd in 7A golf
text:
CHS boys finish 3rd in 7A golf Posted: October 7, 2015 - 9:09pm By David McCollum LOG CABIN STAFF WRITER 
Conway’s boys finished third Wednesday in the 7A boys state golf tourney with a two-round score of 307-310-617 at Fayetteville Country Club. 
Fayetteville won the state title with a 36-hole score of 300-295-595, opening the gap during the second round on Little Rock Catholic (306-302-608). 
Luke Long of Fayetteville was medalist with a two-round score of 70-71-141. Mitchell Ford of Catholic was second at 72-73-145. Blaine Calhoon of Cabot finished was third at 71-75-146. Those golfers qualified for next week’s Overall. 
Whit Parker posted Conway’s best score of 73-74-147, just missing the Overall. Carter Cloe, last year’s runnerup, finished at 75-74-149. Both Parker and Cloe earned all-state honors. 
Other Conway scores were: Grayson McEowen, 79-82-161; Jackson Goodwin 79-81-160; and Clay Bradshaw (85, first round) and Jett Tolliver (85, second round).
